{"/service/ndnp/txdn/batch_txdn_evans_ver01/data/sn86063730/00332893786/1930111302/0237.xml":{"full_text":"KIWANIANS OF\n2 CITIES MEET\nHarlingen Surprises Sister\nCity of San Benito\nWith Program\n(Special to Herald)\nBAN BENITO, Nov. 13.\u2014Hands\nbf friendship were extended across\nUse Arroyo Colorado Wednesday as\nKtwanlane of the twin cities Har\nBngen and San Benito, met to\nlether at the Stonewall Jackson\nbote! and heard inspiring Armistice\nDay talks from Rev. L. A. Boons.\nDew pastor of the Methodist church\n*t Harlingen and J. F. Rodgers,\npostmaster there.\nWhen San Benito Klwanians i\nrived at the hotel they discovered,\nto their surprise, visitors seated on\nalternate chairs at the luncheon\ntable. Probably nonplussed by the\npresence of 40 visiting Klwanians,\nthey were late In coming in.\nPresident W. M. Driskell of the\nHarlingen club, who presided,\npromptly made them spin their\nown tardy wheel to determine\ntheir punishment. Each had to oaT\na small fine.\nThe Rev. Mr. Boon*. a\u2018 one time\nChaplain for the Texas depart\nment of the American Tog^on\nmade an Armistice Day talk In\nwhich he stressed man power a.*\nopposed to man's power or the\nspiritual force a* opposed to com\nmercial gain. He pointed out that\nevery colony planted cn American\nShores for comm^rc'al gain failed\nbut that those which rallied on\naims more worth v survived Not\nbo much reliance should be placed\non machinery and other evidence\nof man's Dower but more on such\nnoble qualities as go toward* mak\ning manpower, he said\nMr Rodgers dwelled on the\ngrowth of communism and other\nforces destructive to government,\npointing out that thev were on\nposed to the princioles for which\nAmerica fought during the World\nWar\nThe program was In charge of\nD. W Dav of Harlingen who re\nferred to the mixups caused by the\nfact that there was a D. W Day\nin San Benito, also a Kiwanian.\nMr. Rodeers similarly made refer\nence to R. W. Nelson of Harlingen\nf' with whom he Is often confused\nbecause of phvsical resemblances\nMrs. Jack Carev of Harlingen\nentertained the Joint meeting with\nseveral vocal solos, being ac\ncompanied by Mrs. S. R. Jennings.\nFour of the aviators present for\nthe San Benito airport celebration\nwere introduced as guests\nHomer Maxwell won the Har\nlingen attendance prize donated bv\nDr Driskell.\nHydrogen, which is an element\nls the lightest substance known to\nscience. Its specific gravity, com\npared with air. is .0695\nCHEVROLET DISPLAYS NEW CAR\nNew 1931 Chevrolet Six Sport Roadster (with rumble seat)\nChevrolet's new car for 1931, priced substantially below current levels, is on display throughout the\nnation. The new car boasts a two-inch increase in wheelbase, larger and roomier bodies by Fisher with\nmohair or broadcloth as optional trimming, and scores of refinements in appearance and performance\ndespite the new prices which bring the level for 'he 1931 car to a far lower figure than any Chevrolet,\nfour or six, has ever sold. Dealers throughout the United States put the new models on exhibition\nnearly two months in advance of the customary date for the showing of the annual new car. This move\nin advancing the announcement date, it was felt bv Chevrolet officials, would render a distinct contribu\ntion to the cause of general business revival by insuring extraordinary activity during two normally\ndull business months for the 200.000 people throughout the United States who depend directly upon\nChevrolet for their livelihood.\nRUBIO FACES\n(Continued From Page One'\ntion and highway construction In\n1031 is the largest in the history\nof Mexico. An educated man him\nself. the president feels that edu\ncation and ample communication\nfacilities are vitally necessary for\nthe development of his country.\nDuring recent months he has per\nsonally authored several measures\ndesigned to make educational fa\ncilities more accessible to his coun\ntrymen.\nEarly completion of the vast\nhighway construction program,\nwhich is being pushed by Minister\nof Communication General Juan\nAndreu Almazan, has a two-fold\npurpose in the president\u2019s recon\nstruction program. Besides offering\nMexicans an opportunity to see\ntheir own country and thus elimi\nnate provincialism, the highways\nwill create a highly profitable\nsource of revenue for the govern\nment and citizens through the In\nflux of tourists.\nAfter submitting the budget for\nnext year to congress. President\nOrtiz Rubio sent to congress a\nmessage, later widely acclaimed by\nthe Mexican press, in which he out\nlined his program for the ambitious\ncampaign which observers sav will\nbe the severest t\u00abst of his ability\nto lead his country\nInvestments Favored\n\u201cThe time has arrived to end\nany movements Intended to aggra\nvate or prevent relief to the pres\nent r-itical condition.\u2019* the presi\ndent said \"It is also time for con\ngrew, to legislate laws establishing\norganic equilibrium between capi\ntal and labor\nThis last remark attracted\nlion not. only in Industrial and la\nbor headauarters o( Mexico but in\nthe United States where manv in\nvestors have delayed th\u00abMr entry\ninto Mexico until the adoption of\nequitable labor laws\n\"We must create a state of con\nfidence to favor Investments.\u201d he\ncontinued \"We realize tha*. this\nrequires settlement of two mator\nproblems. They are the agrarian\nand labor questions, both of which\nconstitute the basis of the revolu\ntionary* program.\u201d\nCongress already is studying\ntentative changes in the labor\nlaws. A few hours after his mes\nsage was delhered. President Ortiz\nRubio sent to congress an am\u00b0nd\nment to the agrarian laws making\nseveral basic changes in their\npresent operation.\nLaws Revised?\nThe president's amendment\nwould exclude from the presmt\nagragrian laws the provision al\nlowing for the taking over for dis\ntribution to peasants lands in pro\nduction of fruit, dairy*, sugar\nvegetable or cattle. Many land\nowners have hesitated to onerato\ntheir haciendas for fear of having\n666\nis a doctor's Prescription for\nColds and Headaches\nIt is the most speedy remedy known\n666 also in Tablets\nH-icm taken o\\*er and distributed\nto peasant*. The amendment also\nrejects the demand of villages for\nenlargement of their communal\na-nds unless they have money on\nhand to pay the landowners. At\npresent land seized paid for in\nfederal agragrian bonds which are\ncashable at about 16 per cent of\ntheir face value.\nThe amendment ai&o would give\nhacienda owners the right to em\nploy larce numbers of peons with\nout being under obligation to give\nthe neons land. It has been the\npractice in the past for peons to\nform a village on the ''aclenda\nemploying them and demand, and\nreceive, communal lands at the\nexpense of the landowner.\n\"It is my determination to take\nwhatever steps are necessary to\nplace the finances of Mexico on a\nsound basis, to carry out both the\ninternal and exterior obligations,\nand to award full protection to\nbofh canital and labor,\u201d the presid\nent further declared.\nConfidence Gained\nAlthough the optimism voiced\nEndorsed By\nBeautiful Women\nBeauties who guard their com\nplexions use MELLO-ULO Face\nPowder only. Famous for purity\u2014\nits coloring matter is approved by\nthe Government Th\u00bb k*ci\"\nlook* pasty or flaky. It spreads\nmore smoothly and p.odu^\nyouthful bloom Made by a ..ew\nFrench process. MELLO-GLO Face\nPowder stays on longer. Cisneros\nDrug Stores\nAtwater IKewt\nRADI 3\nYonr choice today!\nYonr pride in\nyears to eonie\n\u2014the radio with the GOLDEN VOICE\nTo MOST CLEAR-THINKING PEOPLE the\nchoice of a radio is simple. It is an investment in hap\npiness\u2014not for today alone, bnt for yean to come.\ndear reasoning leads directly to Atwater Kent\u2014\nwith eight yean of leadership behind it\u2014with more\nthan THREE MILLION satisfied owners.\nThe same superior workmanship that built np this\npopular preference is responsible for this year's out*\ntone quality\u2014the Golden Voice.\nThe same genius that developed the use of Screen\nGrid is responsible for this season\u2019s exclusive con\nvenience feature --the Quick-Vision DiaL\nThis same resourcefulness perfected Atwater Kent\nTbne Control\u2014with four definite shadings of the\nGolden Voice.\nAnd this same foresight planned the beautiful,\nIfwnniAaivimpiig^ of the new model designs\u2014the\nkind of radio yon Hke to live with.\nTour soundest investment in radio today\u2014and for\nthe years to come is the Atwater Kent with the\nCoUaVoieaftoieitat your dealer\u2019s.\nMODEL 70\nLowboy, $119. Other beautiful\nmodels, including Radio-Phono\ngraph combination, from $125 to\n$195. Prices leas tubes.\nPriam \u2022Ufhthf lughor mml dm Rorkim\nand ui Canada\nATWATER KENT MANUFACTURIN' CO.\nTHREE MILLION SATISFIED OWNERS\nby the president and the j tss here\nsmacks of the determined optim\nistic statements heard in the\nUnited States, the newspapers of\nMexico City point out that the\ncauses of depression in the two\ncountries are exactly opposite. On\nthe whole. Excelsior explains. Mex\nico lias been suffering from a lack\nof production for some time. Crops\nhave been considerably below\nnormal for two successive years\nin all branches of agriculture. The\noil industry has been stagnate,\ntins year's production not quite\nequal to 1929, and manufacturing\nand other industries have been re\ntarded by labor troubles a 1 lack\noi capital.\nFriends of President Ortiz Ku\nbio are firm in their belief that he\nwill emerge as Mexico's greatest\npeacetime leader In his present\ncampaign to bring prosperity to the\ncountry. They point out that his\nadministration, which assumed of\nfice only last February 5. alreadv\nha* created confidence among\nforeign investors They point to the\nrecent entrance into Mexico of the\nNational City Bank of New York\nand the Electric Bond and Share\ncompany, brth of which have made\nstzeable investment in Mexico this\nyear, as examples.\nm\nForrest Easterly\nEnlisted In Navy\nForrest Orley Easterly, son of Mr.\nand Mrs. H M. Martin Easterly of\nBrownsville, was selected from\namong 400 applicants in the South\nTexas district to join the navy, ac\ncording to George Kramer, recruit\ning officer.\nNo boy with less than a high\nschool education is taken but East\nerly also had one year in Browns\nville Junior college.\nThere is only on? negro mem\nber of the U. S. Congress. He is\nOscar De Priest, R-publican from\nChicago.\nRoad Association\nMeets in Houston\nWith prospect* brighter than\never, the Hug-the-Coast highway\nassociation will meet in Houston\nThursday in joint session with two\nother road bodies, it has be\u00b0n an\nnounced by J dge O. C. Dancy, a\ndirectcr In the association.\nH. C. Inms, secretary of the\nbody, states in a letter to Judge\nDancy: \u201cThere are so many things\nto encourage us that we ought to\nlook to the future with much\nconfidence Copano bay is high\nbridged, the crossing over Lavaca\nEnds Headache\nIn One-Half\nUsual Time\nHEADACHES from nerves or eye\nor stomach, pains that fellow\naard, tedious work, can be relievtc\nwith little delay. Capudine, a iquic\npreparation is the new, amasiogl)\ntuick way that is replacing ordinary\npowders and tablets.\nin thousands of homes it has become\nt household remedy kept on hand ai\nill times to end suffering and misery\nrom headaches.\nIcing liquid, Capudine acts tmmedi\nualy, often m one-third the tune re\npur ed by other forms. It contains nc\nlarcotics, does not disturb digestioc\nnd is approved by doctors and drug\nlists. Even with the most sever*\nteadache, relief comes very quickly\nold at Drug Stores, 10c. JOc. and 60c bonle\nod by the dose at soda fouctxios.\nI\nbay is going ahead with dispatch;\ngrading and dint work are in\nprogress from Opano crossing\nnorth toward Tivoli; Brazoria\ncounty is working Galveston county\nwill see that we have a road from\nthere to Orange.**\n\nTOUGHS\n1. Rub on throat: Bloat mn art\ntongue and nraflowaa it melts\n4 visas\nOVER t? MILLION JARS USE0 VEA81Y\n\"An Example of Advancement\"\nSays\nVINCENT BENDIX\nPresident and Chairman of the Board,\nBendix Aviation Corporation of\nChicago and New York, operating\nBendix Brake Company, South Bend,\nIndiana; Eclipse Machine Company,\nElmira, New York; Bendix Stroraberp\nCarburetor Company, South Bend,\nIndiana, and other subsidiaries,\n\"Competition is the life of busi*\nness. To win leadership a manu*\nfacturer must make his product\nmore desirable than others\u2022\nHence there results a great bene\nfit to the public through constant\nstriving for improvement. The\nuse of the modern Ultra \\Tiolet\nRay in toasting the tobaccos\nused in LUCKY STRIKES is an\nexample of such advancement&\nEveryone knows that sun\nshine mellows\u2014that\u2019s why TOASTING\nincludes the use of the Ultra Violet Ray.\nLUCKY STRIKE\u2014the finest cigarette you\never smoked, made of the finest tobaccos\n\u2014the Cream of the Crop\u2014THEN\u2014\"IT\u2019S\nTOASTED.\" Everyone knows that heat\npurifies and so TOASTING removes harm\nful irritants that cause throat irritation and\ncoughing. No wonder 20,679 physicians\nhave stated LUCKIES to be less irritating I\n\u201cIt\u2019s toasted\"\nYour Throat Protection against irritation against cough\nConsistent with its policy of laying the facts before the public. The American Tobacco Company has invited Mr. Vincent\nBendix to review the reports of the distinguished men who have witnessed LUCKY STRIKE\u2019S famous Toasting Process.\nThe statement of Mr. Bendix appears on this page.\n19JO, Tha American Tobacco Co.. Mfra.","height":"36944","width":"27884"}}
